                              <td valign="top" style="font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#333333; font-size:12px; text-align:justify;"><br />
                                The second edition of Ffreedom Takeoff was organised in mid- July 2011 with a view to enhance the client experience at Ffreedom via innovations. <br />
                                <br />
                                The session was conducted by Mr. Bhupender Sharma and focussed on the Need of Financial Planning and Way ahead for Ffreedom. Mr. Sharma is a strategic innovation consultant and the Founder of NXTLYF (an innovation coaching firm). Mr. Sharma had been brought in to identify areas where client satisfaction could be increased via use of innovations in the financial planning sector.  <br />
                                <br />
                                The interactive session began with a discussion on the current problems in the financial industry, especially those which impact the financial plans. Another aspect that was discussed extensively during the interactive session was the changing role of financial planners and how planners need to be cued into the needs of clients in a dynamic market scenario. <br />
                                <br />
                                During the discussion, Mr. Sharma asked all the financial planners to list down their wishlist for clients of Ffreedom. In an open forum, the wish-list of the entire team was discussed, along with identifying the challenges in converting these targets into reality.  <br />
                                <br />

                                Mr. Sumeet Vaid, Founder and CEO, Ffreedom Financial Planners also spoke about how the company has been employing proprietary technology to improve the financial planning experience for clients and elaborated on some of the upcoming developments that are likely to be released later this year.  <br />
                                <br />
                                The session, which was organised with Ffreedom headquarters in Mumbai, also witnessed participation from teams across India from offices like Delhi, Pune and Indore. The teams from the four centres jointly brainstormed with Mr. Sharma and Mr. Vaid covering various facets of improvising the financial planning experience. </td>
